110
00:07:01,845 --> 00:07:03,484
It's Boston lobster pasta.

111
00:07:03,485 --> 00:07:05,204
How did you know it's one of my favorites?

112
00:07:05,205 --> 00:07:07,964
Well, that's because,
on the first day of school

113
00:07:07,965 --> 00:07:11,004
you specifically asked
for Boston lobster pasta for lunch.

114
00:07:11,005 --> 00:07:14,084
It was such a random request,
how could I not remember it?

115
00:07:14,085 --> 00:07:17,284
Hurry up, eat it while it's warm.
How does it taste?

116
00:07:17,285 --> 00:07:18,804
-It's good?
-Is it good!

117
00:07:18,805 --> 00:07:20,244
Where did you get it?

118
00:07:20,245 --> 00:07:23,125
I personally made it myself.

119
00:07:23,205 --> 00:07:25,004
I don't just cook for anyone.

120
00:07:25,005 --> 00:07:26,995
You'd better cherish it.

121
00:07:28,085 --> 00:07:29,405
Don't be smug.

122
00:07:30,325 --> 00:07:32,015
Don't eat too fast.

123
00:07:42,085 --> 00:07:42,925
You...

124
00:07:44,605 --> 00:07:46,785
Why are you staring at me?

125
00:07:48,965 --> 00:07:53,405
How exactly did you
hurt yourself while you were sleeping?

126
00:07:53,485 --> 00:07:55,004
Were you sleepwalking?

127
00:07:55,005 --> 00:07:57,055
That's not what happened.

128
00:08:04,165 --> 00:08:07,684
The egg is still warm.
I can rub your forehead for you.

129
00:08:07,685 --> 00:08:09,555
-Don't--
-Don't move.

130
00:08:19,365 --> 00:08:20,804
-Situ Feng.
-Yes?

131
00:08:20,805 --> 00:08:23,965
When did you start learning how to cook?

132
00:08:25,125 --> 00:08:26,644
